The current iteration is actually the result of trying to solve for getting rid of the redundant generic param for CreateAndRegister<T,U>, as seen here: 
https://github.com/mandyshieh/reef/commit/f67b15abd1993ff217cec836cab0b3afb11c6956

@singlis and I had a lengthy discussion about this. Ideally, it'd be better if the values were stored as specific types, but that would require the user to specify that type along with the metric class on creation(`CreateAndRegisterMetric<IntegerMetric, int>() `instead of just `CreateAndRegisterMetric<IntegerMetric>()`). In the end we concluded that the lesser of two evils would be to make IMetric non-generic to eliminate the possibility of error in CreateAndRegister<T,U> when T and U don't match, especially since this PR contains concrete implementations for most cases so the user doesn't need to implement their own IMetric<U>.

@singlis feel free to chime in if there are points I didn't cover well. Thanks!

